title: Grateful Dead Live at World Music Theater on 1990-07-21
lineage: Transfer:  Fostex D-5 (optical)> M-Audio USB Transit> Audacity @ 16/48> 16/44> CD Wave (tracking)> TLH (SBE's/Flac/md5); Transferred and liberated to etree on October 14, 2014 by Will Petty
description:
Set 1
Touch Of Gray, Greatest Story Ever Told, Jack A Roe, Walkin' Blues, Friend Of The Devil, A Little Light, Queen Jane Approximately, Bird Song
Set 2
Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Playin' In The Band-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Jam-> I Need A Miracle-> Crazy Fingers-> Playin' In The Band Jam-> Dear Mr. Fantasy-> Playin' In The Band, One More Saturday Night
Encore: The Mighty Quinn

reviews.review_text:
Best audience of this one I've heard Cleanest sound overall.  Listen to the Bird Song jam, you can hear every instrument clearly.  The bass is a little boomy, but that's handled by turning down the bass knob or low frequency equalizer settings on playback.  

I've already reviewed the show on one of the soundboards, it's excellent.  A solid 4 stars (I reserve 5 stars for an 80's/90's show for something with a long Dark Star, like 7/12/90).
